19:T498,Internal brochure evidence clearly describes a bare metal coronary stent with hybrid cell design (closed cells at ends, open cells in middle) using cobalt-chromium L605 alloy with 120 µm struts. Specifications indicate large vessel peripheral coronary stenting (5-10mm diameters, 0.035 inch guidewire compatibility, 6-7Fr sheath). The clinical meaning is unambiguous: this is a BMS product family for coronary intervention. However, brand attribution is missing - manufacturer is listed as Meril Life Sciences but no confirmation if 'Myra' is their brand or a third-party brand under license. Large diameter range (5-10mm) and 0.035 inch guidewire compatibility suggests this may be positioned for both coronary and potentially large peripheral vessel applications, though division lists Cardiovascular/Coronary Stents. Send to review to: (1) confirm brand ownership/licensing, (2) clarify if this is truly coronary-only or also peripheral indication given large diameters, (3) verify if 'Myra' represents a broader platform with other products (DES variants). No external sources available to verify. Current classification data is accurate but incomplete for brand context.15:["$","$L18",null,{"product":{"product_name":"Myra BMS","product_name_display":"Myra BMS Bare Metal Stent","sku_code":"MYB","product_family":"Myra BMS","product_family_display":"Myra BMS","slug":"myra-bms","images":[{"id":"8dd9fe97e544","storage_path":"agile-ortho/products/69c4bca6809c1c146658e45e/cover_a2569935.jpg","original_filename":"cover_myra-bms-1702272483pdf.pdf.jpg","content_type":"image/jpeg","size":461758,"uploaded_at":"2026-03-26T05:59:13.969213+00:00","source":"brochure_extraction","width":1654,"height":2339},{"id":"c1579fbf0113","storage_path":"agile-ortho/products/69c4bca6809c1c146658e45e/cover_9db26658.jpg","original_filename":"cover_myra-bms-1702272483pdf.pdf.jpg","content_type":"image/jpeg","size":461758,"uploaded_at":"2026-03-26T06:03:24.679540+00:00","source":"brochure_extraction","wi